<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-12"><hi rend="italic">June 12,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Hay approves suggestions in Mr. Rockhill’s telegrams of the 11th instant
                        and directs to do what he can for speedy conclusion; and, if practicable to
                        obtain them, to agree to 5 per cent effective with compensations
                        mentioned.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>